Here is my friend Max who thought he wasn't photogenic üòÇüòÇüòÇüòÇ. I would like to take this opportunity to address the famous point of photogenics.
A photographer is supposed to bring out the best of you on your portrait... in the same way he enhances a landscape (if he does both like me)... So if the picture is not good it is never your fault, but the photographer's who didn't know how to do his job .

However, there are some people who do not like the way their portrait looks, not because the picture is not good, but because they are not used to seeing themselves this way. And that's a whole other debate.

What do you think about of the picture ?  Are you one of those who think they are not photogenic?

The first time I noticed this little man under Pont Neuf near Daurade, I was quite surprised. I thought It was a red devil because the horns on his head and had no idea of how it got there. I asked people, did research and found out it was representing a child punished and excluded from the society. The child represents minorities, or social exclusion in general. The donkey cap gives the idea of someone who doesn't fit in the boxes, who is alone. 
All the credit go to the artist James Colomina .Hats off Sir!!
